---
import FridayHarborLayout from '../../layouts/FridayHarborLayout.astro';
import { entries } from '../../data/friday-harbor';
const entry = entries.find(e => e.slug === '2026-04-25-eye-of-the-needle')!;
---
<FridayHarborLayout entry={entry}>
  <figure slot="figure" class="hormuz-figure">
    <div class="hormuz-stage" id="stage" aria-label="Map of the Strait of Hormuz">
      <p class="map-status">
        <span data-lang="en">Loading map...</span>
        <span data-lang="zh">地图加载中...</span>
      </p>
    </div>
    <figcaption data-lang="en">
      <b>How a 39-km strait edits the world's oil.</b>
      Iran on the north shore, Oman's Musandam exclave on the south.
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-pin"></span>
        <span><b class="event-mark">①</b> M/V Ararat (24 Apr) &nbsp; <b class="event-mark">②</b> M/V Heron Star (25 Apr) — both seized within visual range of the Iranian-held islands of Qeshm, Larak, and Hormuz.</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>
    <figcaption data-lang="zh">
      <b>一条 39 公里的海峡，如何改写世界石油的命运。</b>
      北岸是伊朗，南岸是阿曼飞地穆桑代姆半岛。
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-pin"></span>
        <span><b class="event-mark">①</b> 阿拉拉特号（4 月 24 日） &nbsp; <b class="event-mark">②</b> 苍鹭星号（4 月 25 日）—— 两次扣船均发生在伊朗管辖的格什姆、拉腊克、霍尔木兹三岛视野之内。</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <aside class="hormuz-stats" aria-label="strait of Hormuz key figures">
      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">21<small>&nbsp;mb / day</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">crude oil through the strait</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">2,100<small>&nbsp;万桶 / 日</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">原油经此海峡运出</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">≈ 20<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">of the world's seaborne oil</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 20<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">全球海运原油占比</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">39<small>&nbsp;km</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">narrowest navigable reach</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">39<small>&nbsp;公里</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">可通航最窄处</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">≈ $1.7<small>&nbsp;B / day</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">daily crude value through</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 17<small>&nbsp;亿美元 / 日</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">每日通过的原油价值</span>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </figure>

  <div slot="notebook-en">
    <p>
      Most of the world's oil that travels by sea travels through here.
      The narrowest navigable channel inside the strait is about 39 kilometres
      across. Big tankers don't have a third of that to manoeuvre in:
      the international Traffic Separation Scheme gives outbound and inbound
      traffic a single 3-kilometre lane each, with a buffer between.
    </p>
    <p>
      What that geometry means is that <em>a small country with a long
      coastline on the right side</em> can interrupt one of the planet's
      biggest economic arteries with relatively little. Iran's Bandar Abbas
      sits just inside the channel; the islands of Qeshm, Larak and Hormuz
      give it close-in vantage. The two seizures this week were both within
      visual range of those islands.
    </p>
    <p>
      Cartographically the choice I made on this map is the small one:
      I kept the view <em>flat and tight</em>. Newsroom maps of the same week
      reach for a tilted satellite perspective; that style is good for the
      eye but bad for measuring. A flat top-down map lets a reader put a
      finger on the seizure pin and a finger on Khasab and see, without help,
      how short that distance really is.
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>A small disclosure.</em> The seizure pins are placed from open AIS
      reports and may shift as positions are corrected. The shipping-lane
      drawing follows the Traffic Separation Scheme but is sketched, not
      survey-grade.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div slot="notebook-zh">
    <p>
      全世界海上运输的原油，大部分都从这里过。海峡里可通航的最窄处约 39 公里宽。
      可大型油轮真正能动的水面远没有这么宽：国际航道分隔系统给进、出两个方向
      各划出 3 公里宽的单向航道，中间留一条缓冲。
    </p>
    <p>
      这条几何形状意味着：<em>一个海岸线正好长在'对的那一边'的小国</em>，
      只需要很有限的力量，就能切断地球上最重要的几条经济动脉之一。
      伊朗的阿巴斯港正好就坐在水道边，外加格什姆岛、拉腊克岛、霍尔木兹岛
      构成的近距离观察哨位。这周的两次扣船，都发生在这些岛屿的视野之内。
    </p>
    <p>
      在制图上我做的选择只有一个小决定：保持<em>正射、平面、贴近</em>。
      这一周新闻里那些图，多数喜欢用倾斜卫星视角——那种风格悦目，但不便于测量。
      一张正俯视的图，让读者一根手指按在扣船标记上、另一根按在哈萨布上，
      不用任何辅助就能看见——这两点之间的距离究竟有多近。
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>附注：</em>扣船标记按公开 AIS 报告放置，未来如有修订两侧同步更新。
      航道走向参照国际航道分隔系统，但为示意性绘制，并非测绘等级。
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul slot="provenance-en">
    <li>Coastline &amp; admin boundaries: <a href="https://www.naturalearthdata.com/downloads/10m-physical-vectors/" rel="noopener">Natural Earth 1:10m</a> via the <code>martynafford/natural-earth-geojson</code> distribution; <code>world-atlas@2</code> 1:50m as fallback.</li>
    <li>Strait baseline traffic: <a href="https://www.eia.gov/todayinenergy/detail.php?id=55339" rel="noopener">EIA, World Oil Transit Chokepoints</a> — approximately 21 million barrels a day, ≈ 20% of global seaborne oil (2023 estimate).</li>
    <li>Daily crude value: 21 mb/d × ≈ $80 / barrel ≈ $1.7 B / day (rough order of magnitude).</li>
    <li>Channel width: International Hydrographic Organization charts; minimum navigable channel ≈ 21 nautical miles ≈ 39 km.</li>
    <li>Vessel-seizure positions (illustrative): open-source AIS reporting, 24–25 April 2026. Subject to revision.</li>
    <li>Source map &amp; build script: <code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-25-eye-of-the-needle.astro</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <ul slot="provenance-zh">
    <li>海岸线与行政边界：<a href="https://www.naturalearthdata.com/downloads/10m-physical-vectors/" rel="noopener">Natural Earth 1:10m</a>，经 <code>martynafford/natural-earth-geojson</code> 分发；<code>world-atlas@2</code> 1:50m 作 fallback。</li>
    <li>海峡基线流量：<a href="https://www.eia.gov/todayinenergy/detail.php?id=55339" rel="noopener">EIA《世界石油海运咽喉点》</a>——约 2,100 万桶 / 日，约占全球海运原油的 20%（2023 年估算）。</li>
    <li>每日原油货值：2,100 万桶 / 日 × 约 80 美元 / 桶 ≈ 17 亿美元 / 日（量级近似）。</li>
    <li>水道宽度：国际海道测量组织海图；可通航最窄处约 21 海里 ≈ 39 公里。</li>
    <li>扣船坐标（示意）：开源 AIS 报告，2026 年 4 月 24–25 日。位置可能后续修订。</li>
    <li>源码与构建脚本：<code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-25-eye-of-the-needle.astro</code>。</li>
  </ul>
</FridayHarborLayout>

<style>
  .hormuz-figure { margin: 0; }
  .hormuz-stage {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 5 / 4;
    background: transparent;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }
  .hormuz-stage svg { display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
  .map-status {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .hormuz-figure figcaption {
    margin: 1.1rem 0.2rem 0;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 880px;
  }
  .hormuz-figure figcaption b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }
  .hormuz-figure figcaption .event-mark { color: var(--rose); font-weight: 600; }
  .hormuz-figure figcaption em { color: var(--uw-purple-deep); font-style: italic; }
  .hormuz-figure figcaption .legend-line {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }
  .hormuz-figure figcaption .legend-swatch {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    width: 28px; height: 14px;
    margin-top: 4px;
    position: relative;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .swatch-route {
    background: linear-gradient(to right,
      var(--bg-card) 0 6px, transparent 6px 13px,
      var(--bg-card) 13px 20px, transparent 20px 27px,
      var(--bg-card) 27px 28px);
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--uw-purple-deep);
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--uw-purple-deep);
    border: 0;
    background-color: rgba(245,239,226,0.55);
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px var(--rule);
  }
  .swatch-route::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 2px; right: 2px; top: 6px; height: 2px;
    background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(to right,
      var(--uw-purple-deep) 0 5px, transparent 5px 10px);
  }
  .swatch-pin {
    background: var(--rose);
    border: 1.4px solid var(--uw-purple-deep);
    border-radius: 50%;
    width: 14px; height: 14px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(194,160,148,0.32);
  }

  /* Hard-numbers strip — concretises the geopolitical/economic stakes */
  .hormuz-stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.4rem;
    margin: 1.4rem 0.2rem 0;
    padding: 1rem 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .hormuz-stats .stat {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }
  .hormuz-stats .stat-num {
    font-family: var(--display, "Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 1.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--uw-purple-deep);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums lining-nums;
  }
  .hormuz-stats .stat-num small {
    font-size: 0.55em;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-left: 0.1em;
  }
  .hormuz-stats .stat-label {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-width: 14em;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .hormuz-stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem; }
  }
  .aside {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--rule);
    padding-left: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: 0.88rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>

<script type="module">
  import * as d3 from 'https://esm.sh/d3@7';
  import { feature } from 'https://esm.sh/topojson-client@3';

  // Frame matches the reference satellite image: Iran south coast at top,
  // Persian Gulf at left, the strait centre-right, Gulf of Oman lower-right,
  // UAE / Oman desert at the bottom.
  const STRAIT = [56.30, 26.55];
  const VIEW_WINDOW = {
    west:  53.00,
    east:  58.40,
    south: 23.00,
    north: 27.40
  };
  // IMO Traffic Separation Scheme.  The line spans the entire frame, from the
  // far-west Persian Gulf (well south of the Iranian coast at lon 54°, which
  // had been clipping the previous start point) all the way SE to the deep
  // Gulf of Oman.  Routed SOUTH of Qeshm — that's the actual TSS path.
  const STRAIT_CORRIDOR = [
    [53.00, 25.80],   // ★ west-edge entry, deep in Persian Gulf
    [53.70, 25.85],
    [54.40, 25.85],
    [55.00, 25.95],
    [55.50, 26.05],
    [55.90, 26.15],
    [56.20, 26.35],   // turn NE into the strait
    [56.45, 26.55],   // narrowest reach
    [56.65, 26.55],
    [56.80, 26.45],   // east of Musandam tip
    [57.00, 26.25],
    [57.25, 25.85],   // entering Gulf of Oman
    [57.55, 25.30],
    [57.85, 24.50]    // ★ south-east exit, deep Gulf of Oman
  ];

  const SEIZURES = [
    { date: '2026-04-24', lon: 56.20, lat: 26.40, label: { en: 'M/V Ararat',     zh: '阿拉拉特号' } },
    { date: '2026-04-25', lon: 56.55, lat: 26.55, label: { en: 'M/V Heron Star', zh: '苍鹭星号' } }
  ];

  const CITIES = [
    // Iranian north shore (in frame across the wider view)
    { name: { en: 'Bandar Lengeh', zh: '伦格港'   }, lon: 54.88, lat: 26.55 },
    { name: { en: 'Bandar Abbas',  zh: '阿巴斯港' }, lon: 56.27, lat: 27.18 },
    { name: { en: 'Bandar Jask',   zh: '贾斯克港' }, lon: 57.78, lat: 25.65 },
    // Strait + Musandam (Oman exclave)
    { name: { en: 'Khasab',        zh: '哈萨布'   }, lon: 56.25, lat: 26.21 },
    // UAE
    { name: { en: 'Dubai',         zh: '迪拜'     }, lon: 55.27, lat: 25.27 },
    { name: { en: 'Fujairah',      zh: '富查伊拉' }, lon: 56.34, lat: 25.13 }
  ];

  // Strait islands — only the largest gets a label at this scale.
  // (Larak and Hormuz are tiny; their names crowded the Strait-of-Hormuz label.
  //  They're still drawn as land; just unlabeled.)
  const ISLANDS = [
    { name: { en: 'Qeshm I.', zh: '格什姆岛' }, lon: 55.85, lat: 26.65 }
  ];

  // Oil & gas terminals — small rose squares.
  // (Bandar Abbas terminal removed: redundant with the city dot at the same spot.)
  const TERMINALS = [
    { name: 'Lavan',       lon: 53.30, lat: 26.80 },
    { name: 'Sirri',       lon: 54.55, lat: 25.90 },
    { name: 'Hengam',      lon: 55.85, lat: 26.65 },
    { name: 'Khor Fakkan', lon: 56.35, lat: 25.34 },
    { name: 'Fujairah',    lon: 56.34, lat: 25.13 }
  ];

  // (Annotation callouts removed — leader lines made the page noisy.
  //  All factual annotations live in the figcaption and notebook below.)

  const css = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement);
  const c = {
    paper:   css.getPropertyValue('--bg-card').trim()   || '#f5efe2',
    paper2:  css.getPropertyValue('--bg-deep').trim()   || '#ddd4c2',
    rule:    css.getPropertyValue('--rule').trim()      || '#d6cdbf',
    ink:     css.getPropertyValue('--ink').trim()       || '#2c2823',
    inkSoft: css.getPropertyValue('--ink-soft').trim()  || '#6c6358',
    inkFaint:css.getPropertyValue('--ink-faint').trim() || '#98907f',
    purple:  css.getPropertyValue('--uw-purple').trim() || '#6a5a6e',
    purpleD: css.getPropertyValue('--uw-purple-deep').trim() || '#4a3e4d',
    sage:    css.getPropertyValue('--sage').trim()      || '#8e9c8a',
    sageS:   css.getPropertyValue('--sage-soft').trim() || '#b4bdaf',
    rose:    css.getPropertyValue('--rose').trim()      || '#c2a094',
    mist:    css.getPropertyValue('--mist').trim()      || '#a8b1b3',
  };

  let _land = null;
  let _borders = null;

  const NE = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/martynafford/natural-earth-geojson@master/10m';

  Promise.all([
    fetch(`${NE}/physical/ne_10m_land.json`).then(r => r.ok ? r.json() : Promise.reject()),
    fetch(`${NE}/cultural/ne_10m_admin_0_boundary_lines_land.json`).then(r => r.ok ? r.json() : Promise.reject()),
  ])
  .then(([landGJ, borderGJ]) => {
    _land    = landGJ;
    _borders = borderGJ;
    requestAnimationFrame(() => draw());
  })
  .catch(() => {
    // fallback: world-atlas 50m countries (less ideal — has admin breaks in fill)
    fetch('https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/world-atlas@2/countries-50m.json')
      .then(r => r.json())
      .then(w => {
        _land = feature(w, w.objects.countries);
        _borders = null;
        requestAnimationFrame(() => draw());
      });
  });

  window.addEventListener('resize', () => { if (_land) draw(); });

  const fhRoot = document.querySelector('.fh-root');
  if (fhRoot) {
    new MutationObserver(() => { if (_land) draw(); })
      .observe(fhRoot, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['data-lang'] });
  }

  function currentLang() {
    return fhRoot && fhRoot.getAttribute('data-lang') === 'zh' ? 'zh' : 'en';
  }

  function draw() {
    const land = _land;
    const borders = _borders;
    if (!land) return;
    const stage = document.getElementById('stage');
    if (!stage) return;

    const W = stage.clientWidth | 0;
    const H = stage.clientHeight | 0;
    if (W < 50 || H < 50) { requestAnimationFrame(() => draw()); return; }

    stage.innerHTML = '';
    const svg = d3.select(stage).append('svg')
      .attr('viewBox', `0 0 ${W} ${H}`)
      .attr('width', W).attr('height', H)
      .style('display', 'block')
      .style('overflow', 'hidden');
    const lang = currentLang();

    const padL = 2, padR = 2, padT = 2, padB = 4;
    const mapW = W - padL - padR;
    const mapH = H - padT - padB;
    if (mapW < 50 || mapH < 50) return;

    const mercatorY = lat => Math.log(Math.tan(Math.PI / 4 + lat * Math.PI / 360));
    const lonSpan = (VIEW_WINDOW.east - VIEW_WINDOW.west) * Math.PI / 180;
    const ySpan = mercatorY(VIEW_WINDOW.north) - mercatorY(VIEW_WINDOW.south);
    const scale = Math.min(mapW / lonSpan, mapH / ySpan) * 0.98;
    const centerLon = (VIEW_WINDOW.west + VIEW_WINDOW.east) / 2;
    const centerLat = (VIEW_WINDOW.south + VIEW_WINDOW.north) / 2;
    const projection = d3.geoMercator()
      .center([centerLon, centerLat])
      .scale(scale)
      .translate([padL + mapW / 2, padT + mapH / 2])
      .clipExtent([[padL, padT], [padL + mapW, padT + mapH]])
      .precision(0.1);
    const path = d3.geoPath(projection);

    // Site-native Morandi palette — lightened version: cream land, pale mist sea.
    const SEA       = c.mist;       // #a8b1b3
    const SHOAL     = c.sageS;      // #b4bdaf — soft sage for coastal halo
    const LAND      = c.paper;      // #f5efe2 — site cream (lightest), gives the figure the same paper as the rest of the page
    const COAST_DK  = c.inkSoft;    // #6c6358
    const COAST_LT  = 'rgba(108,99,88,0.26)';
    const FOCUS     = c.purpleD;    // #4a3e4d
    // Deep terracotta for pin centres — sits in the rose family but with
    // enough drop in lightness to actually pop against the muted palette.
    const EVENT_DEEP = '#8a3e2e';

    function addText(g, text, x, y, attrs = {}) {
      const halo = g.append('text')
        .attr('x', x).attr('y', y)
        .attr('stroke', attrs.halo || 'rgba(245,239,226,0.86)')
        .attr('stroke-width', attrs.haloWidth || 3.5)
        .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round')
        .attr('paint-order', 'stroke')
        .attr('fill', attrs.fill || c.ink)
        .attr('font-family', attrs.fontFamily || 'Inter, "Noto Sans CJK", sans-serif')
        .attr('font-size', attrs.fontSize || 10.5)
        .attr('font-weight', attrs.fontWeight || 500)
        .attr('font-style', attrs.fontStyle || 'normal')
        .attr('letter-spacing', attrs.letterSpacing || 0)
        .attr('text-anchor', attrs.anchor || 'middle')
        .text(text);
      return halo;
    }

    const clipId      = 'fh-mapclip';
    const seaGradId   = 'fh-seagrad';
    const hillshadeId = 'fh-hillshade';
    const seabedId    = 'fh-seabed';

    const defs = svg.append('defs');
    defs.append('clipPath').attr('id', clipId)
      .append('rect').attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT).attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH);

    // SEA DEPTH GRADIENT — lightened: the deepest stop now sits at the
    // page's --mist value, with shallower water trending toward bg-deep.
    const seaGrad = defs.append('linearGradient').attr('id', seaGradId)
      .attr('gradientUnits', 'userSpaceOnUse')
      .attr('x1', padL + mapW / 2).attr('y1', padT)
      .attr('x2', padL + mapW / 2).attr('y2', padT + mapH);
    seaGrad.append('stop').attr('offset', '0%').attr('stop-color', '#d2d8d6');   // very pale shoal
    seaGrad.append('stop').attr('offset', '55%').attr('stop-color', '#bcc4c4');  // mid mist
    seaGrad.append('stop').attr('offset', '100%').attr('stop-color', '#a8b1b3'); // = --mist (deepest)

    // ========== TRUE HILLSHADE FILTER (land) ==========
    // feTurbulence -> noise = synthetic terrain bumpmap
    // feDiffuseLighting + feDistantLight (NW, 45° elevation)  =  shaded relief
    // feComposite operator="in" against SourceGraphic = clip to land path
    // filterUnits=userSpaceOnUse + explicit bounds = WORKS on world-scale paths
    // (this is the trick that fixes the earlier silent-failure problem).
    const hill = defs.append('filter').attr('id', hillshadeId)
      .attr('filterUnits', 'userSpaceOnUse')
      .attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT)
      .attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH)
      .attr('color-interpolation-filters', 'sRGB');
    hill.append('feTurbulence')
      .attr('type', 'fractalNoise')
      .attr('baseFrequency', '0.012')   // low freq → rolling hills, not noise
      .attr('numOctaves', '4')
      .attr('seed', '11')
      .attr('result', 'hnoise');
    const hLight = hill.append('feDiffuseLighting')
      .attr('in', 'hnoise')
      .attr('surfaceScale', '4')
      .attr('diffuseConstant', '1.0')
      .attr('lighting-color', '#e2d2a8')   // muted Morandi-warm sun (low saturation)
      .attr('result', 'hshade');
    hLight.append('feDistantLight').attr('azimuth', '315').attr('elevation', '50');
    hill.append('feComposite')
      .attr('in', 'hshade').attr('in2', 'SourceGraphic').attr('operator', 'in');

    // ========== SEABED RIDGE FILTER (sea) ==========
    // Same idea, lower contrast, light from a different angle so reads as
    // "underwater" relief, not a second hillshade.
    const sea = defs.append('filter').attr('id', seabedId)
      .attr('filterUnits', 'userSpaceOnUse')
      .attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT)
      .attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH)
      .attr('color-interpolation-filters', 'sRGB');
    sea.append('feTurbulence')
      .attr('type', 'fractalNoise')
      .attr('baseFrequency', '0.018')
      .attr('numOctaves', '3')
      .attr('seed', '23')
      .attr('result', 'snoise');
    const sLight = sea.append('feDiffuseLighting')
      .attr('in', 'snoise')
      .attr('surfaceScale', '2.0')
      .attr('diffuseConstant', '0.85')
      .attr('lighting-color', '#c5cdcf')   // light mist — same family as the sea, just lighter
      .attr('result', 'sshade');
    sLight.append('feDistantLight').attr('azimuth', '290').attr('elevation', '28');

    // Sky tab outside the sphere
    svg.append('rect').attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT)
      .attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH).attr('fill', c.paper2);

    // All geography clipped to the map area
    const mapG = svg.append('g').attr('clip-path', `url(#${clipId})`);

    // SEA — depth gradient
    mapG.append('rect').attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT)
      .attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH)
      .attr('fill', `url(#${seaGradId})`)
      .attr('stroke', 'none');

    // SEABED RELIEF — barely there, just enough to break flat sea
    mapG.append('rect').attr('x', padL).attr('y', padT)
      .attr('width', mapW).attr('height', mapH)
      .attr('filter', `url(#${seabedId})`)
      .attr('opacity', 0.18)
      .style('mix-blend-mode', 'multiply');

    // Subtle graticule: map ticks, not decoration.
    mapG.append('g').selectAll('path').data(d3.geoGraticule().step([0.5, 0.5]).lines())
      .join('path').attr('d', path).attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', c.rule).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.22).attr('stroke-width', 0.4);

    // BATHYMETRY: a wider pale-blue stroke under the land creates a halo of
    // shallow water around all coast — without any filter (those failed earlier
    // because the source path is world-scale).
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', SHOAL)
      .attr('stroke-width', 8)
      .attr('stroke-opacity', 0.55);
    // A second narrower band, slightly darker, gives the halo two-step gradation
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', c.sage)
      .attr('stroke-width', 2.2)
      .attr('stroke-opacity', 0.32);

    // LAND base fill — drawn first; the hillshade overlay multiplies on top
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', LAND)
      .attr('stroke', COAST_LT)
      .attr('stroke-width', 1.8)
      .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round');

    // HILLSHADE — multiplied at lower opacity so it shades the cream land
    // gently without making it look muddy.
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('filter', `url(#${hillshadeId})`)
      .attr('fill', '#ffffff')
      .attr('opacity', 0.38)
      .style('mix-blend-mode', 'multiply');

    // Crisp dark coastline on top
    mapG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', COAST_DK)
      .attr('stroke-width', 0.8)
      .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round')
      .attr('stroke-linecap', 'round');

    // Country borders — clearer dashed line so the political geometry is
    // legible against the desert hillshade
    if (borders) {
      mapG.append('path').datum(borders).attr('d', path)
        .attr('fill', 'none')
        .attr('stroke', 'rgba(74,62,38,0.78)')
        .attr('stroke-width', 0.85)
        .attr('stroke-dasharray', '5 3')
        .attr('stroke-linecap', 'round');
    }

    // (Shipping-corridor line, arrowhead, and inline TSS label removed —
    //  the dashed line drifting across open sea was not earning its visual
    //  weight; the strait IS the lane.)

    // Fonts declared once, up-front
    const seaSerif = lang === 'zh'
      ? '"Noto Serif SC", "Songti SC", "STSong", serif'
      : '"Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif';
    const islandSerif = seaSerif;

    // "39 km narrowest" call-out — shortened and bumped north into clear water
    // east of Musandam tip so it no longer collides with the Khasab label.
    const notePoint = projection([56.95, 26.45]);
    if (notePoint) {
      addText(mapG,
        lang === 'zh' ? '最窄处约 39 公里' : 'narrowest reach · 39 km',
        notePoint[0], notePoint[1], {
          fill: FOCUS,
          fontSize: lang === 'zh' ? 11 : 10.5,
          fontWeight: 650,
          haloWidth: 4
        });
    }

    // ----- Labels (plain forEach — no fragile each+remove) -----

    // Sea / water-body names. Strait of Hormuz moved SE into clear water so it
    // no longer collides with the seizure pins, the 39-km callout, or Larak I.
    const seaLabels = lang === 'zh'
      ? [ { t: '波斯湾',         lon: 53.65, lat: 25.20, size: 22, weight: 500, sp: '0.55em', italic: true },
          { t: '阿曼湾',         lon: 57.95, lat: 24.55, size: 22, weight: 500, sp: '0.55em', italic: true },
          { t: '霍尔木兹海峡',   lon: 57.20, lat: 25.85, size: 14, weight: 400, sp: '0.42em', italic: true } ]
      : [ { t: 'Persian Gulf',     lon: 53.65, lat: 25.20, size: 19, weight: 500, sp: '0.42em', italic: true },
          { t: 'Gulf of Oman',     lon: 57.95, lat: 24.55, size: 19, weight: 500, sp: '0.42em', italic: true },
          { t: 'Strait of Hormuz', lon: 57.20, lat: 25.85, size: 13, weight: 400, sp: '0.45em', italic: true } ];
    const seaG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-labels-sea');
    seaLabels.forEach(d => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      addText(seaG, d.t, p[0], p[1], {
        fill: c.purpleD,
        fontFamily: seaSerif,
        fontStyle: d.italic ? 'italic' : 'normal',
        fontWeight: d.weight || 400,
        fontSize: d.size,
        letterSpacing: d.sp || '0.08em',
        halo: 'rgba(245,239,226,0.85)',
        haloWidth: 3.5
      });
    });

    // Island names — italic, slightly larger, more letter-spacing
    const islandG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-labels-islands');
    ISLANDS.forEach(d => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      addText(islandG, d.name[lang], p[0], p[1] - 7, {
        fill: c.inkSoft,
        fontFamily: islandSerif,
        fontStyle: 'italic',
        fontSize: 11.5,
        letterSpacing: '0.10em',
        halo: 'rgba(245,239,226,0.92)',
        haloWidth: 3.5
      });
    });

    // Oil & gas terminals — rose squares
    const termG = mapG.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-terminals');
    TERMINALS.forEach(d => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      termG.append('rect')
        .attr('x', p[0] - 3.5).attr('y', p[1] - 3.5)
        .attr('width', 7).attr('height', 7)
        .attr('fill', c.rose).attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1);
    });

    // Country labels — Iran is biggest by virtue of having the most landmass
    // in frame; Oman and U.A.E. share the same secondary tier (sovereign equals).
    const countryLabels = lang === 'zh'
      ? [ { t: '伊朗',   lon: 55.40, lat: 27.20, size: 34, sp: '0.55em' },
          { t: '阿曼',   lon: 57.85, lat: 23.30, size: 28, sp: '0.55em' },
          { t: '阿联酋', lon: 54.50, lat: 24.40, size: 28, sp: '0.45em' } ]
      : [ { t: 'IRAN',   lon: 55.40, lat: 27.20, size: 30, sp: '0.55em' },
          { t: 'OMAN',   lon: 57.85, lat: 23.30, size: 25, sp: '0.50em' },
          { t: 'U.A.E.', lon: 54.50, lat: 24.40, size: 25, sp: '0.42em' } ];
    const countrySerif = seaSerif;
    const countryG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-labels-country');
    countryLabels.forEach(d => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      addText(countryG, d.t, p[0], p[1], {
        fill: c.purpleD,
        fontFamily: countrySerif,
        fontStyle: lang === 'zh' ? 'normal' : 'italic',
        fontWeight: 500,
        fontSize: d.size || 14,
        letterSpacing: d.sp || (lang === 'zh' ? '0.22em' : '0.20em'),
        halo: 'rgba(245,239,226,0.92)',
        haloWidth: 5
      });
    });

    // City dots — bigger labels for the wider frame
    const cityG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-cities');
    CITIES.forEach(d => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      const g = cityG.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${p[0]},${p[1]})`);
      g.append('circle').attr('r', 2.8).attr('fill', c.ink)
        .attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1.4);
      addText(g, d.name[lang], 7, 4, {
        fill: c.ink,
        fontSize: 12,
        fontWeight: 600,
        anchor: 'start',
        halo: 'rgba(245,239,226,0.92)',
        haloWidth: 3.5,
        letterSpacing: lang === 'zh' ? '0.04em' : '0.02em'
      });
    });

    // Seizure pins — numbered (① ②). The CENTRE is now a deep terracotta
    // (sits in the rose family but ≈ 35% darker) so it pops against the
    // pale putty/mist palette. Outer rings stay rose for the soft pulse.
    const numerals = ['①', '②', '③', '④', '⑤'];
    const pinG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-pins');
    SEIZURES.forEach((d, i) => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      const g = pinG.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${p[0]},${p[1]})`);
      const phase = (i * 1.4).toFixed(1);
      // outer attention ring — rose pulse
      const outer = g.append('circle').attr('r', 17).attr('fill', 'none')
        .attr('stroke', c.rose).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.65).attr('stroke-width', 1.5);
      outer.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'r')
        .attr('values', '14;22;14').attr('dur', '2.4s').attr('begin', `-${phase}s`).attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
      outer.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'stroke-opacity')
        .attr('values', '0.75;0.10;0.75').attr('dur', '2.4s').attr('begin', `-${phase}s`).attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
      // inner halo
      const halo = g.append('circle').attr('r', 9).attr('fill', c.rose).attr('fill-opacity', 0.42)
        .attr('stroke', c.rose).attr('stroke-width', 1);
      halo.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'r')
        .attr('values', '7;12;7').attr('dur', '2.4s').attr('begin', `-${phase}s`).attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
      halo.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'fill-opacity')
        .attr('values', '0.50;0.20;0.50').attr('dur', '2.4s').attr('begin', `-${phase}s`).attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
      // dot — DEEP terracotta for contrast
      g.append('circle').attr('r', 5).attr('fill', EVENT_DEEP)
        .attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1.3);
      // numeral — deep terracotta with cream halo, placed clear of the pulsing
      // outer ring (max radius 22px; (20,-16) ≈ 26px from centre)
      const numText = g.append('text').attr('x', 20).attr('y', -16)
        .attr('fill', EVENT_DEEP).attr('font-size', 19).attr('font-weight', 700)
        .attr('font-family', 'Inter, "Noto Sans CJK", sans-serif')
        .attr('paint-order', 'stroke')
        .attr('stroke', 'rgba(245,239,226,0.95)')
        .attr('stroke-width', 3.5)
        .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round')
        .text(numerals[i] || (i + 1));
      numText.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'opacity')
        .attr('values', '1;0.50;1').attr('dur', '2.4s').attr('begin', `-${phase}s`).attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
    });

    // Scale bar — pinned to bottom-left of map area, with 0 / 25 / 50 ticks
    const refLat = STRAIT[1];
    const totalKm = 50;
    const halfKm  = 25;
    const degLonTotal = totalKm / (111 * Math.cos(refLat * Math.PI / 180));
    const degLonHalf  = halfKm  / (111 * Math.cos(refLat * Math.PI / 180));
    const ra = projection([STRAIT[0], refLat]);
    const rb = projection([STRAIT[0] + degLonTotal, refLat]);
    const rh = projection([STRAIT[0] + degLonHalf,  refLat]);
    if (ra && rb && rh) {
      const barPx  = Math.abs(rb[0] - ra[0]);
      const halfPx = Math.abs(rh[0] - ra[0]);
      const x0 = padL + 22;
      const y0 = padT + mapH - 28;
      const sg = svg.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${x0}, ${y0})`);
      // bar
      sg.append('line').attr('x2', barPx).attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-width', 1.1);
      // ticks
      [0, halfPx, barPx].forEach(x => {
        sg.append('line').attr('x1', x).attr('x2', x).attr('y1', -4).attr('y2', 4)
          .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-width', 1.1);
      });
      // labels
      sg.append('text').attr('x', 0).attr('y', -7).attr('text-anchor', 'middle')
        .attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-size', 9).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif').text('0');
      sg.append('text').attr('x', halfPx).attr('y', -7).attr('text-anchor', 'middle')
        .attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-size', 9).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif').text('25');
      sg.append('text').attr('x', barPx).attr('y', -7).attr('text-anchor', 'middle')
        .attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-size', 9).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif').text(`${totalKm} km`);
    }

    // ===== LOCATOR INSET — orthographic globe, top-right =====
    // A small reference globe so readers know where on Earth this map sits.
    const inSize = 116;
    const inMargin = 14;
    const inX = padL + mapW - inSize - inMargin;
    const inY = padT + inMargin;
    const cR = inSize / 2;            // globe radius

    const inG = svg.append('g')
      .attr('class', 'fh-inset')
      .attr('transform', `translate(${inX}, ${inY})`);

    // Soft frame in site cream
    inG.append('rect')
      .attr('x', -10).attr('y', -10)
      .attr('width', inSize + 20).attr('height', inSize + 28)
      .attr('fill', c.paper)               // paper cream
      .attr('stroke', c.rule)              // warm hairline
      .attr('stroke-width', 0.8)
      .attr('rx', 4);

    // Orthographic projection centred on the strait
    const inProj = d3.geoOrthographic()
      .scale(cR - 1)
      .translate([cR, cR])
      .rotate([-STRAIT[0], -STRAIT[1], 0])
      .clipAngle(90);
    const inPath = d3.geoPath(inProj);

    // Sphere fill = pale mist (matches main map's lightened sea)
    inG.append('path').datum({ type: 'Sphere' }).attr('d', inPath)
      .attr('fill', '#bcc4c4')                         // mid-mist (lighter)
      .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft)
      .attr('stroke-opacity', 0.7)
      .attr('stroke-width', 0.7);

    // Faint graticule
    inG.append('g').selectAll('path').data(d3.geoGraticule().step([20, 20]).lines())
      .join('path').attr('d', inPath).attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', 'rgba(245,239,226,0.45)').attr('stroke-width', 0.35);

    // Land = warm putty (slightly deeper than the page paper for separation)
    inG.append('path').datum(land).attr('d', inPath)
      .attr('fill', c.paper2)                          // #ddd4c2
      .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft)
      .attr('stroke-opacity', 0.55)
      .attr('stroke-width', 0.35);

    // Mark the location — deep terracotta for the same contrast pop as main pins
    const sp = inProj(STRAIT);
    if (sp) {
      inG.append('circle').attr('cx', sp[0]).attr('cy', sp[1])
        .attr('r', 7).attr('fill', 'none')
        .attr('stroke', c.rose).attr('stroke-width', 1.4)
        .attr('stroke-opacity', 0.9);
      inG.append('circle').attr('cx', sp[0]).attr('cy', sp[1])
        .attr('r', 3).attr('fill', EVENT_DEEP);
    }

    // Caption below the globe
    addText(inG,
      lang === 'zh' ? '霍尔木兹海峡' : 'Strait of Hormuz',
      cR, inSize + 12, {
        fill: c.inkSoft,
        fontFamily: seaSerif,
        fontStyle: 'italic',
        fontSize: 10,
        fontWeight: 500,
        letterSpacing: lang === 'zh' ? '0.18em' : '0.12em',
        haloWidth: 2.5,
        halo: 'rgba(245,239,226,0.92)'
      });

    // No north arrow: at this scale the coastlines and labels orient the reader.
  }

  // (lang re-render is wired up at the top, with a cached `_land`.)
</script>
